Defendant Gonzalo Anguiano in court with attorney Valeria Lenise Taylor.  Defendant Gonzalo Anguiano in custody.  Patrick J Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Additional statements by: Sandy D.

As to Count 1:
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 9 MONTHS at the House of Corrections with 84 days credit CONSECUTIVE to any other sentence or count.

As to Count 2:
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 3 MONTHS at the House of Corrections with 0 days credit CONSECUTIVE to any other sentence or count.

As to Count 3:
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 3 MONTHS at the House of Corrections with 0 days credit CONSECUTIVE to any other sentence or count.

Court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on 2 YEARS probation.

  Conditions of Probation:
- Successfully complete an anger management class.
- Successfully complete a cognitive thinking class if deemed appropriate by the department.
- Successfully complete a parenting class if deemed appropriate by the department.
- Work towards GED or HSED.
- Obtain/maintain fulltime employment/education/vocation.  Must work a minimum of 20 hours/week.
- No contact with: Ismael S or Liliana A.
- Follow all rules of supervision and follow through with any other treatment deemed necessary by the department.

Court ordered the defendant pay all of the following by the end of supervision.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment:
Restitution in the amount of $6,312.29 payable to Ismael S- FIRST PRIORITY; 
All court costs, fees, and surcharges (including DNA); 
All applicable fees of supervision.
-  Cash bail on deposit to be applied.

Filed:  
Victim Impact Statement    
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief
Pre-trial Incarceration Credit

Court ordered defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.

As to Counts 1-3:
Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  Case adjourned for sentencing in Branch 22 on 02/04/2015 at 8:30am.

Defendant Gonzalo Anguiano in court with attorney Valeria Lenise Taylor.  Michael Lonski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Filed, original amended information; copy served on defendant.  Defendant acknowledges receipt of information, waives formal reading, and Court enters a plea of not guilty.  
Court ordered Counts 1 amended to Misdemeanor Battery, Party to a Crime, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 940.19(1), 939.51(3)(a), 939.05, a Class A Misdemeanor.
